The earth awakens with the dawn,
Birdsong pierces the morning still,
Sunbeams stretch across the land,
Kissing petals aglow with dew.

In this tapestry of colors,
I find my spirit dance and soar,
Connected to the essence of life,
A reminder of nature’s endless grace.

- Jessie Redmon Fauset
